The paper discusses modifications and extensions to the Cnvlutin (CNV) accelerator for convolutional and fully-connected layers of Deep Learning Network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AR (Hardware Architecture for Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on optimizing memory usage and energy consumption, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper specifically mentions convolutional layers, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
